  "method": [
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Heat the oven to 220°C. Take the chicken out of the fridge about 30 mins before roasting – it cooks more evenly that way."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Halve the lemon. Crush the garlic cloves with the flat side of a knife, leaving the skins on. Stuff the chicken cavity with the lemon halves, garlic and thyme."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Drizzle the chicken all over with olive oil. Get stuck in and rub it in properly. Season generously with salt and black pepper."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Pop the chicken breast-side up in a roasting tray. Roast for about 50 mins–1 hr, or until the juices run clear when you pierce the thickest part of the thigh.\nFor this recipe used a 1.5kg-2kg chicken, adjust the timings for a smaller or larger bird."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Let it rest for at least 15 mins before carving – it’ll be much juicier, promise."
    }
